{
  "uuid": "c19b51d3aa92e98c36ad5a80b3def85c",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Production Store Supervisor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><em><strong>Daily Store Operations</strong></em></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Manage the day-to-day running of the store that supports production and site installation teams</li>\n  <li>Receive, label, store, and issue tools, materials, and consumables in an organised and timely manner</li>\n  <li>Ensure that items are neatly stored, well-labelled, and easy to access</li>\n  <li>Maintain cleanliness and proper housekeeping in the store at all times</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><em><strong>Issuance and Tracking</strong></em></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Track movement of frequently used items (e.g. adhesives, blades, sealants) and update records accordingly</li>\n  <li>Maintain a manual or digital log of items issued to staff or jobs</li>\n  <li>Monitor the return of reusable tools and equipment</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><em><strong>System Setup &amp; Improvement</strong></em></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assist management in setting up a basic inventory tracking system (Excel, manual logs, or software)</li>\n  <li>Recommend improvements to the store layout, labelling, or process to improve efficiency and accountability</li>\n  <li>Help establish min/max stock levels for key consumables</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><em><strong>Stock Monitoring &amp; Replenishment</strong></em></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conduct periodic stock checks and highlight low-stock items</li>\n  <li>Prepare purchase requests for commonly used materials and tools in advance</li>\n  <li>Liaise with Procurement or Purchasing staff to ensure timely restocking</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><em><strong>Tool Care &amp; Reporting</strong></em></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Check and report damaged or missing tools</li>\n  <li>Ensure proper storage and handling of equipment to minimise loss or misuse</li>\n  <li>Keep a record of high-value tools checked out to individuals or teams</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum 3 years of experience in a store or stockroom role, preferably in construction, fabrication, or manufacturing</li>\n  <li>Familiar with tools and materials used in stone or worktop fabrication is a strong advantage</li>\n  <li>Able to work independently and responsibly</li>\n  <li>Comfortable with manual handling of items (within safe limits)</li>\n  <li>Proficient in using Excel or simple inventory logs</li>\n  <li>Organised, trustworthy, and detail-oriented</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Preferred but Not Required</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Experience in setting up or improving manual stock control systems</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with adhesives, abrasives, blades, and other materials related to fabrication and installation</li>\n  <li>Forklift license or experience operating store equipment is a bonus</li>\n</ul>",
